<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881107-0012 </DOCNO><HL> Eastern Penalized for Drugs </HL><SO> </SO><CO> TEX </CO><IN> AIR MON </IN><G> TRE </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Customs Service said it is penalizing Eastern Airlines $1.8 million after seizing cocaine from one of the carrier's airplanes.    A Customs Service spokesman said Eastern, a unit of Texas Air Corp., has been sent notice of the penalty, which will stand unless the airline appeals within 30 days. Under a 1986 law, airlines are subject to penalties of $1,000 for each ounce of cocaine found.    The drug was seized from a plane in Miami Oct. 31.    Eastern officials couldn't be reached for comment. </TEXT></DOC>